HEADWORD: -ist
<hw>-ist</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧sh"⟦usl⟧*⟦icr⟧st)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>-iste</ets>.]</ety> <def>A noun suffix denoting an
<sig>agent</sig>, or <sig>doer</sig>, <sig>one who practices</sig>, a
<sig>believer in</sig>; <as>as, theor<ex>ist</ex>, one who theorizes;
social<ex>ist</ex>, one who holds to socialism; sensual<ex>ist</ex>, one
given to sensuality.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

